Repented bandits surrender 203 sophisticated arms in Zamfara
Surrendering

By Ibrahim G. Ahmad
08061675474
Gusau May 26, 2021 (NAN) Zamfara State Government has confirmed the surrendering of 203 sophisticated firearms by  repented  bandits and volunteer group (Yansakai) under the state government peace accord.
The Commission for Security and Home Affairs, Alhaji Garba Dauran disclosed this at a press briefing which held in Gusau on Monday.
Dauran added that 2,566 live ammunitions, 64 magazines, 2 handcuffs and 887 locally fabricated Dane guns were also surrendered to the state.
He said internal security operation had  achieved a lot in the state through the peace reconciliation process which led to the return of normalcy in some hard hit areas.
He said despite that,  all hands must be on deck to check attacks on soft targets.






